xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees

Class STRBulkLoader<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees.AbstractIterativeRtreeBulkloader<T>
      • xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees.STRBulkLoader<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IterativeBulkLoaderInterface<T>

    public class STRBulkLoader<T>
extends AbstractIterativeRtreeBulkloader<T>
    This class implements STR loading algorithm by Leutenegger et al.: See: Scott Leutenegger and Mario A. Lopez and J. Edgington STR: A Simple and Efficient Algorithm for R-Tree Packing (ICDE 1997) For storing temporal level data simple file is used.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      STRBulkLoader(RTree rtree, String path, int dimension, int blockSize, double ratio, double nodeUtil, int[] sortingFunction)
      For initializing the STR loader we need an Rtree, number of dimensions, blocksize, storage utilization per node in percent and so called sortign function this provides the ordering of dimensions, since str sorts and partitions data according to one dimension at one step sorting function provides which dimension should be taken as next e.g. in two dimensional space we have 4 different sorting functions x,x or x,y or y,y, or x,x in this example we use a default one x,y

        For initializing the STR loader we need an Rtree, number of dimensions, blocksize, storage utilization per node in percent and so called sortign function this provides the ordering of dimensions, since str sorts and partitions data according to one dimension at one step sorting function provides which dimension should be taken as next e.g. in two dimensional space we have 4 different sorting functions x,x or x,y or y,y, or x,x in this example we use a default one x,y
        Parameters:
        rtree -
        path -
        dimension -
        blockSize -
        ratio - is used after loading for R* split
        nodeUtil - based on this value maximal entries per node are computed
        sortingFunction -
